WEBVTT

00:01.132 --> 00:04.605
NINA! ARE YOU HOME,
BABY?

00:04.605 --> 00:07.108
ARE YOU IN THE BATHROOM?

00:07.108 --> 00:10.381
[WOOD CREAKING]

00:12.083 --> 00:14.215
UGH.

00:19.050 --> 00:21.192
UH, MAYBE I SHOULD
COME BACK ANOTHER TIME.

00:21.192 --> 00:25.196
[GROWLING]

00:26.026 --> 00:27.728
OH. OOPS.

00:29.500 --> 00:31.602
IS THAT BETTER?

00:31.602 --> 00:33.734
UH, WHAT'S THAT?

00:33.734 --> 00:36.737
OH, I JUST WENT
FOR SOME TAKEOUT.

00:36.737 --> 00:38.769
I WASN'T EXPECTING
COMPANY,

00:38.769 --> 00:42.243
NOT THAT I MIND
A SURPRISE VISIT.

00:42.773 --> 00:43.544
SO, WHAT'S UP?

00:43.544 --> 00:45.816
WELL, UM, I WAS
ON MY WAY TO WORK,

00:45.816 --> 00:50.151
AND I DECIDED I WANT
TO INTRODUCE YOU
TO MY FRIENDS.

00:50.151 --> 00:53.824
REALLY? THAT'S GREAT!

00:56.127 --> 00:57.188
YEAH. IT--IT
IS GREAT.

00:57.188 --> 01:00.591
UM, WELL, HERE'S
THE STORY WE'RE
GONNA TELL THEM.

01:00.591 --> 01:01.632
THERE'S A STORY?

01:01.632 --> 01:02.733
WE MET AT A MALL.

01:02.733 --> 01:03.464
I WAS SHOPPING
FOR PANTS,

01:03.464 --> 01:06.197
AND YOU AND I GOT
INTO A FIGHT FOR
THE LAST PAIR.

01:06.197 --> 01:07.738
IT WAS INSTANT
CHEMISTRY. BOOM!

01:07.738 --> 01:12.103
BOOM. BEN, I DON'T
THINK THAT'S GONNA BE
A VERY GOOD STORY.

01:12.103 --> 01:14.245
IT IS. IT HAPPENS
ALL THE TIME.

01:14.245 --> 01:15.546
AND AFTER SOME TIME
PASSES

01:15.546 --> 01:19.280
AND THE GUYS GET
TO KNOW YOU AND SEE
HOW AWESOME YOU ARE,

01:19.280 --> 01:22.082
THEN WE'LL TELL THEM
YOU'RE A DEMON FROM
HELL AND ALL THAT.

01:22.082 --> 01:24.555
YOU'RE ASHAMED OF ME.
YOU'RE ASHAMED
OF ME, AREN'T YOU?

01:24.555 --> 01:25.856
YOU'RE ASHAMED
THAT I'M A DEMON.

01:25.856 --> 01:27.087
WHAT? NO, THAT'S
CRAZY. NO.

01:27.087 --> 01:30.161
I JUST--MY FRIENDS
MIGHT HAVE A PROBLEM
WITH THE FACT

01:30.161 --> 01:33.364
THAT YOU TRIED TO
KILL SAM THAT ONE
TIME,

01:33.364 --> 01:34.195
BUT THAT'S ALL.

01:34.195 --> 01:38.098
IT'S NOT LIKE I TRIED
TO MURDER YOUR FRIEND
FOR FUN, BEN.

01:38.098 --> 01:40.171
I WAS REBELLING
AGAINST SATAN,

01:40.171 --> 01:41.372
AND SAM IS IS
RIGHT HAND.

01:41.372 --> 01:44.605
I WAS BASICALLY
BEING A HERO.

01:44.605 --> 01:48.809
ANYWAY, CAN WE PLEASE
MOVE PAST THIS?

01:48.809 --> 01:50.441
IT WOULD JUST BE
FOR A LITTLE WHILE,

01:50.441 --> 01:52.843
AND I'LL KNOW THAT
THEY'LL BE CRAZY
ABOUT YOU

01:52.843 --> 01:55.446
THE WAY I AM.

01:55.716 --> 01:59.490
WILL YOU DO THIS
FOR ME, PLEASE?

02:01.252 --> 02:04.355
OK, FINE.
I'LL DO IT,

02:04.355 --> 02:07.528
BUT THE SECOND THAT
THEY THINK THEY'RE
CRAZY ABOUT ME,

02:07.528 --> 02:08.229
WE TELL THEM.

02:08.229 --> 02:11.732
ABSOLUTELY.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.136
TASTES LIKE PENNIES.

02:16.136 --> 02:18.909
THAT'S JUST BLOOD,
SILLY.

02:18.909 --> 02:21.742
I'M GONNA GO
WASH UP.

02:23.844 --> 02:26.317
SAY, ARE YOU JUST
WASHING YOUR HANDS

02:26.317 --> 02:28.819
OR TAKING A FULL SHOWER?

02:28.819 --> 02:31.882
BECAUSE I COULD HELP.

02:31.882 --> 02:35.756
[CREAKING]

02:38.659 --> 02:42.193
ACTUALLY, I'M LATE FOR WORK.

02:42.193 --> 02:50.901
♪♪

02:51.302 --> 02:53.904
IT'S DIFFICULT WHEN A MEMBER
OF YOUR FAMILY

02:53.904 --> 02:55.806
IS REMOVED FROM YOUR LIFE,

02:55.806 --> 02:58.349
FORCIBLY OR OTHERWISE,

02:58.349 --> 03:00.851
AND WE WANT TO MAKE THIS TIME
OF TRANSITION

03:00.851 --> 03:04.655
AS SMOOTH AND PAINLESS
AS POSSIBLE.

03:04.655 --> 03:05.716
WITH THAT IN MIND,

03:05.716 --> 03:07.918
WE LOOKED OVER THE PERSONNEL
FROM THIS STORE,

03:07.918 --> 03:10.761
AND WE FEEL
THAT WE HAVE MADE

03:10.761 --> 03:11.962
AN EXCELLENT
DECISION...

03:11.962 --> 03:13.364
SURPRISE.

03:13.364 --> 03:14.365
ANDI...
WHAT?

03:14.365 --> 03:15.566
THE FLOOR IS YOURS.

03:15.566 --> 03:17.328
NO WAY. YOU'RE
OUR NEW MANAGER?

03:17.328 --> 03:18.198
NO WAY, SAM.

03:18.198 --> 03:20.401
YOU'RE BANGING
OUR NEW MANAGER.
SHUT UP.

03:20.401 --> 03:20.871
HEY, EVERYBODY...

03:20.871 --> 03:22.973
LISTEN, I JUST WANT TO SAY
THAT I KNOW FIRST-HAND

03:22.973 --> 03:24.675
HOW HARD EVERYBODY WORKS HERE,

03:24.675 --> 03:25.976
AND DON'T WORRY, YOU KNOW,

03:25.976 --> 03:28.909
I'M NOT GONNA GET ALL CRAZY
WITH POWER OR ANYTHING.

03:28.909 --> 03:29.880
HA HA!
HA HA!

03:29.880 --> 03:31.982
ALSO, I'M NOT ABOVE
BUYING YOUR AFFECTION,

03:31.982 --> 03:35.646
SO WHY DON'T WE JUST
KICK THE DAY OFF WITH A PRIZE?

03:35.646 --> 03:37.248
A PRIZE?
HA HA!

03:37.248 --> 03:39.990
I'VE GOT ONE GIFT CERTIFICATE
TO THE COFFEE SHACK

03:39.990 --> 03:41.292
FOR ONE LUCKY WINNER.

03:41.292 --> 03:48.329
AND THAT WINNER IS...
LES NESSMAN.

03:48.329 --> 03:49.900
YEAH! LES, WHERE ARE YOU?

03:49.900 --> 03:50.861
LES, GET UP.
OH, HE'S NOT HERE. OK.

03:50.861 --> 03:54.905
OK, HEY, EVERYBODY,
LES NESSMAN COULDN'T
BE HERE TODAY

03:54.905 --> 03:56.407
'CAUSE HE'S OUT
ON A LUMBER DELIVERY,

03:56.407 --> 03:58.939
SO I AM GLAD TO ACCEPT
THIS GIFT CERTIFICATE

03:58.939 --> 04:00.271
ON HIS BEHALF.

04:00.271 --> 04:00.971
THANK YOU.

04:00.971 --> 04:02.012
WHO IS LES NESSMAN?

04:02.012 --> 04:04.715
HE AND I HAVE
A SQUASH GAME
LATER ON.

04:04.715 --> 04:06.517
I WILL MAKE SURE
THAT HE GETS THIS.

04:06.517 --> 04:08.879
DON'T YOU WORRY.

04:09.950 --> 04:13.484
I GOT YOU A LITTLE SOMETHING
TO SAY CONGRATULATIONS.

04:13.484 --> 04:16.287
SORRY, WE WERE OUT
OF NUMBER ONE BOSS MUGS.

04:16.287 --> 04:17.928
THANK YOU.
THAT'S VERY SWEET.

04:17.928 --> 04:19.990
I'M SORRY THAT
I SPRUNG THIS ON YOU.

04:19.990 --> 04:22.262
CORPORATE MADE ME
PROMISE NOT TO SAY
ANYTHING

04:22.262 --> 04:24.295
UNTIL THE OFFICIAL
ANNOUNCEMENT.

04:24.295 --> 04:25.366
ARE YOU MAD?
NO.

04:25.366 --> 04:27.638
REALLY? OK, SO YOU'RE
COOL WITH THIS?

04:27.638 --> 04:29.700
I MEAN, ME BEING
YOUR BOSS AND
EVERYTHING.

04:29.700 --> 04:30.341
YEAH, DEFINITELY.

04:30.341 --> 04:32.843
I MEAN, NOTHING'S GONNA
CHANGE BETWEEN US, RIGHT?

04:32.843 --> 04:34.705
OF COURSE NOT.

04:35.546 --> 04:38.849
OK. OH, ACTUALLY,
UM...

04:38.849 --> 04:40.951
DO YOU KNOW THIS
LES NESSMAN GUY?

04:40.951 --> 04:42.653
I MEAN, I'VE NEVER
EVEN HEARD OF HIM.

04:42.653 --> 04:44.885
UH, LES, YEAH.
HE'S GREAT. GOOD--

04:44.885 --> 04:48.389
I GOT TO GET BACK
TO WORK. GOOD TALK, OK?

04:49.920 --> 04:50.861
HEY, GUYS.

04:50.861 --> 04:51.922
HEY, BENJI.

04:51.922 --> 04:53.964
YOU GUYS WANT TO GO GET
A DRINK?

04:53.964 --> 04:54.925
OH, HELLS YES.

04:54.925 --> 04:56.597
NO, NOT NOW.
TONIGHT.

04:56.597 --> 04:58.329
THERE'S SOMEBODY
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET.

04:58.329 --> 05:00.871
WHOA, BEN,
DID YOU MEET A GIRL?

05:00.871 --> 05:01.932
WHOA. WHEN DID YOU
MEET A GIRL?

05:01.932 --> 05:03.474
I NEEDED
A LITTLE ME TIME,

05:03.474 --> 05:05.476
SO I WENT TO THE
MALL ALONE...
SURE.

05:05.476 --> 05:06.477
TO BUY A COUPLE PAIR
OF PANTS.

05:06.477 --> 05:07.878
I'M SORRY.
YOU BOUGHT A COUPLE
PAIR OF PANTS?

05:07.878 --> 05:10.040
SINCE WHEN DO YOU
NEED MORE THAN ONE
PAIR OF PANTS?

05:10.040 --> 05:11.542
WHAT ARE YOU,
JUDE LAW?

05:11.542 --> 05:13.444
AH, POINT IS,
I WENT TO THE MALL

05:13.444 --> 05:15.816
AND MET A GIRL,
NICE, NORMAL GIRL,

05:15.816 --> 05:17.348
AND I'D LIKE HER
TO MEET YOU.

05:17.348 --> 05:18.419
YEAH, WE WOULD
LOVE TO.

05:18.419 --> 05:19.990
THAT SOUNDS LOVELY.
SET IT UP, ALL RIGHT?

05:19.990 --> 05:21.352
WHOA. WHERE
ARE YOU GOING?

05:21.352 --> 05:22.953
OH, BENJI GOT ME ALL PSYCHED
FOR A DRINK.

05:22.953 --> 05:24.555
I'M GONNA GO HAVE
A COCKTAIL BREAK.

05:24.555 --> 05:25.596
BENJAMIN, COME ON.

05:25.596 --> 05:26.657
WHY WOULD I GO?

05:26.657 --> 05:27.628
BECAUSE YOU,
MY FRIEND,

05:27.628 --> 05:29.960
MAKE A GRASSHOPPER
LIKE NOBODY ELSE CAN, OK?

05:29.960 --> 05:31.902
THANK YOU.
DON'T ASK
QUESTIONS.

05:31.902 --> 05:32.963
YEAH, YOU GUYS GO AHEAD.

05:32.963 --> 05:36.036
I'LL JUST STAY HERE
AND WORK. THAT'S COOL.

05:37.938 --> 05:39.970
Woman: AND I HAD TO
GO AROUND THE HOUSE

05:39.970 --> 05:43.874
COLLECTING THE HIDDEN
WHISKEY BOTTLES,

05:43.874 --> 05:44.915
ONE BY ONE.

05:44.915 --> 05:48.048
I GUESS THAT'S ALL
I HAVE TO SAY TONIGHT.

05:48.048 --> 05:49.650
[MURMURING]

05:49.650 --> 05:53.854
THAT'S WHAT IT'S ALL ABOUT,
PEOPLE--STAYING STRONG.

05:53.854 --> 05:57.057
EACH AND EVERY ONE OF US
IS HERE FOR THE SAME REASON--

05:57.057 --> 05:58.028
WE'RE WEAK.

05:58.028 --> 06:02.963
BUT WE MUST ALSO REMEMBER
THE STRENGTH OF THE INDIVIDUAL.

06:02.963 --> 06:07.498
WITH THAT IN MIND, I'D LIKE
TO STEP IT UP A LITTLE BIT.

06:07.498 --> 06:10.801
BARB, WHAT IS
YOUR FAVORITE DRINK?

06:10.801 --> 06:13.804
A LOVE A NICE
IRISH CAR BOMB.

06:13.804 --> 06:14.405
AN IRISH CAR BOMB?

06:14.405 --> 06:18.148
TONIGHT, I WANT YOU TO
GO TO YOUR OLD WATERING HOLE,

06:18.148 --> 06:20.951
AND I WANT YOU TO ORDER
AN IRISH CAR BOMB.

06:20.951 --> 06:26.016
HA! I KNOW, BUT THAT'S
WHAT I WANT YOU ALL TO DO.

06:26.016 --> 06:28.018
TONIGHT, YOU GO TO A BAR,

06:28.018 --> 06:29.990
AND I WANT YOU TO ORDER
YOUR FAVORITE POISON.

06:29.990 --> 06:33.163
AND THEN I WANT YOU
TO WALK AWAY.

06:33.163 --> 06:37.698
THAT'S POWER, PEOPLE,
POWER OVER YOUR ADDICTION.

06:37.698 --> 06:41.902
SO LET'S GO DO IT, HUH?
YES!

06:44.635 --> 06:46.977
VERY GOOD, BARBARA.
THANK YOU.

06:46.977 --> 06:49.139
AH, HA HA,
DON'T LET ME DOWN, CARL.

06:49.139 --> 06:51.582
COUNTING ON YOU, BABE.

06:52.042 --> 06:53.884
BE STRONG.

06:55.616 --> 06:56.447
HA HA!

06:56.447 --> 06:58.989
YOU ARE A TERRIBLE
PERSON, SERIOUSLY.

06:58.989 --> 06:59.890
THAT'S MY JOB, MAN.

06:59.890 --> 07:01.922
YOU KNOW,
TEMPTING THE WEAK,

07:01.922 --> 07:02.993
CULLING THE HERD.

07:02.993 --> 07:04.154
YOU KNOW THE DRILL.

07:04.154 --> 07:08.198
NOW, I WANT YOU
TO MAKE A FIST.

07:08.198 --> 07:10.430
GO AHEAD.

07:11.061 --> 07:13.534
NICE. SOLID, STRONG.

07:13.534 --> 07:15.806
YOU'RE GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT.

07:19.640 --> 07:21.872
HA HA.

07:33.153 --> 07:34.224
BOXING GLOVES?

07:34.224 --> 07:36.156
I'M SUPPOSED
TO BOX A SOUL NOW?

07:36.156 --> 07:40.731
HE GOES BY THE NAME
OF MICHAEL "RED" SABATINO,

07:40.731 --> 07:41.662
A REAL CHUMP.

07:41.662 --> 07:44.495
HE TOOK A PAYOFF IN THE FIFTIES
AND THREW A FIGHT.

07:44.495 --> 07:46.897
THEY BUSTED HIM,
AND THEY DRUMMED HIM
OUT OF THE SPORT.

07:46.897 --> 07:51.171
AND NOW HE'S AFTER
THE ONE THING THAT
ELUDED HIM HIS WHOLE LIFE--

07:51.171 --> 07:53.003
THE CHAMPIONSHIP
HE NEVER WON.

07:53.003 --> 07:55.946
YOU ARE AWARE
THAT I KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT BOXING, RIGHT?

07:55.946 --> 07:57.848
RELAX. RED'S GOT
A WEAK SPOT.

07:57.848 --> 08:02.553
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS
LAND ONE PUNCH ON THE CHIN.

08:02.553 --> 08:03.884
LIGHTS OUT.

08:03.884 --> 08:05.716
IT'S GONNA BE
A PIECE OF CAKE.

08:05.716 --> 08:08.759
ALL RIGHT NOW.
CLEAR OUT OF HERE.

08:08.989 --> 08:12.663
I'VE GOT A SEXAHOLICS GROUP
COMING IN AT 5:00.

08:12.663 --> 08:17.027
TENDS TO BE
A LITTLE MESSY. HA HA!

08:26.707 --> 08:31.281
MMM. I HAVE NEVER EVER
HAD COOKED COW BEFORE.

08:31.281 --> 08:33.013
THIS IS SO GOOD.

08:33.013 --> 08:34.514
SHE LIKES HER BURGERS RARE.

08:34.514 --> 08:36.847
SO, NINA,
WHERE YOU FROM?

08:39.119 --> 08:40.290
I'M FROM THE KANSAS.

08:40.290 --> 08:43.894
UH, THE STATE OF KANSAS.
KANSAS THE STATE.

08:43.894 --> 08:45.295
OK. YEAH,
BEN WAS TELLING US

08:45.295 --> 08:47.027
THAT YOU GUYS MET
AT THE MALL.

08:47.027 --> 08:48.298
BOOM.

08:48.298 --> 08:50.000
BOOM. HEY, NINA,
CHECK THIS OUT.

08:50.000 --> 08:52.002
WHAT DO YOU THINK
IS YOUR BIGGEST
CHARACTER FLAW?

08:52.002 --> 08:54.635
SOCK. YOU DON'T HAVE
TO ANSWER THAT.

08:54.635 --> 08:55.906
SHH. HOLD ON.
I JUST WANT TO
FIND OUT

08:55.906 --> 08:56.767
WHAT WE'RE IN FOR.

08:56.767 --> 08:58.538
I DON'T WANT HER
TO CRUSH HIM LIKE
CASSIDY DID.

08:58.538 --> 09:00.971
WHO'S CASSIDY?

09:00.971 --> 09:02.072
AN OLD FLAME.

09:02.072 --> 09:03.844
SHE STEPPED
OUT ON HIM

09:03.844 --> 09:05.015
WHILE HE WAS
IN THE POKEY.

09:05.015 --> 09:07.047
WHAT'S THE POKEY?

09:07.047 --> 09:07.978
IT'S PRISON.

09:07.978 --> 09:10.050
BABE, WHY WERE YOU
IN PRISON?

09:10.050 --> 09:11.181
IT'S A LONG STORY.
I--

09:11.181 --> 09:13.824
MY EX-WIFE
DOUBLE-CROSSED ME.

09:13.824 --> 09:16.126
SHE TOOK MY MONEY
AND LEFT ME HOLDING
THE BAG

09:16.126 --> 09:18.158
FOR OUR SHAM
GREEN CARD MARRIAGE.

09:18.158 --> 09:20.060
PLUS SHE WAS
A LIMEY. GROSS.

09:20.060 --> 09:24.294
WOW. YOU ARE
A HORRIBLE JUDGE
OF CHARACTER

09:24.294 --> 09:26.196
WHEN IT COMES
TO WOMEN.

09:26.196 --> 09:27.067
YEAH.

09:27.067 --> 09:28.298
SO, ANITA,
WHAT'S YOUR DEAL, THEN?

09:28.298 --> 09:29.970
YOU SOME KIND
OF MURDERER OR SOMETHING?

09:29.970 --> 09:30.971
SHE'S NOT A MURDERER!

09:30.971 --> 09:36.877
OH. OK, BEN. SORRY.
I WAS JUST KIDDING.

09:36.877 --> 09:38.248
OH, I AM STUFFED.

09:38.248 --> 09:40.350
DOES ANYBODY WANT
HALF MY BURGER?

09:40.350 --> 09:42.282
I DO.
Ben: NINA, NO!

09:42.282 --> 09:45.015
OH, JEEZ!

09:46.987 --> 09:48.819
WHY'D YOU DO THAT?

09:48.819 --> 09:53.894
I WANTED TO EAT HIS MEAT
BEFORE THOSE GUYS GOT IT.

09:53.894 --> 09:55.295
YEAH, NINA, NICE.

09:55.295 --> 09:57.297
I LIKE A GIRL
WHO EATS LIKE
A TRUCKER.

09:57.297 --> 09:59.700
THANK YOU, SOCK.

10:06.306 --> 10:07.738
THIS IS WHERE THE SOUL
IS SUPPOSED TO BE.

10:07.738 --> 10:10.681
YEAH? GETTING
A LITTLE NERVOUS TO
THROW DOWN WITH HIM?

10:10.681 --> 10:11.712
IT'S JUST ONE PUNCH.

10:11.712 --> 10:13.043
BESIDES, THE DEVIL SAID
HE WAS A CHUMP.

10:13.043 --> 10:16.016
ALL RIGHT, TOUGH GUY,
LET'S DO IT.

10:26.356 --> 10:27.728
GYM'S CLOSED.

10:27.728 --> 10:31.101
WE'RE--
WE'RE NOT HERE TO WORK OUT!

10:31.101 --> 10:33.704
THE DEVIL SENT ME!

10:35.666 --> 10:35.966
YEAH.

10:35.966 --> 10:40.340
WELL, THEN,
STEP INTO MY OFFICE.

10:42.372 --> 10:45.275
"STEP INTO MY OFFICE."

10:49.850 --> 10:51.081
UH!

10:52.282 --> 10:52.953
HA HA.

10:52.953 --> 10:55.325
YOU'RE NOT GONNA START CRYING
ON ME, ARE YOU?

10:55.325 --> 10:59.089
I'M NOT GONNA CRY.
LET'S FIGHT.

10:59.089 --> 11:01.061
GO ON, KNOCK HIM.
POP HIM, POP HIM.

11:01.061 --> 11:03.694
YOU KNOW WHO I AM,
SLUGGO?

11:03.694 --> 11:04.194
HUH?

11:04.194 --> 11:05.165
I'M RED SABATINO,

11:05.165 --> 11:10.000
THE SAME RED SABATINO
WHO RACKED UP A 33-1 RECORD.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.441
UHH!

11:11.972 --> 11:16.707
AND 29 OF THOSE
WERE KNOCKOUTS.

11:16.707 --> 11:18.078
AAH!

11:18.078 --> 11:19.349
AAH AAH AAH!

11:19.349 --> 11:23.714
AND 11 OF THOSE
WENT IN THE FIRST ROUND.

11:23.714 --> 11:24.955
OH!

11:25.315 --> 11:26.416
WALK IT OFF,
WALK IT OFF,
WALK IT OFF!

11:26.416 --> 11:29.920
I WAS THE BEST THERE WAS,
POUND FOR POUND, KID.

11:29.920 --> 11:32.262
AND THEY SIC A TOMATO
CAN IN AFTER ME?

11:32.262 --> 11:34.424
I'M INSULTED.

11:37.697 --> 11:39.429
AAH!

11:40.070 --> 11:42.933
THAT WAS ME
AT ABOUT 10%.

11:42.933 --> 11:46.306
YOU COME BACK AGAIN,
AND I'LL KILL YOU.

11:46.306 --> 11:47.407
[GROANS]

11:47.407 --> 11:49.740
TELL THE DEVIL
I AIN'T GOING BACK.

11:49.740 --> 11:51.241
YES, SIR.
THANK YOU, SIR.

11:51.241 --> 11:54.084
WELL DONE.

11:54.084 --> 11:57.187
AT LEAST YOU WON
THE MORAL VICTORY.

11:57.187 --> 11:58.949
[BELL RINGS]

12:07.727 --> 12:10.230
HEY, BOSS.
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

12:10.230 --> 12:12.732
HEY. YEAH. COME IN.

12:12.732 --> 12:13.103
MM-HMM.

12:13.103 --> 12:14.434
UM, YEAH.
I'VE BEEN TRYING

12:14.434 --> 12:15.866
TO FIND THIS
LES NESSMAN GUY.

12:15.866 --> 12:18.969
REALLY? THAT S.O.B.
WIN ANOTHER LATTE OR WHAT?

12:18.969 --> 12:20.811
NO. WHAT I THOUGHT
WAS WEIRD

12:20.811 --> 12:22.212
IS THAT I'VE
NEVER MET HIM,

12:22.212 --> 12:23.473
AND WE'VE BOTH
WORKED HERE

12:23.473 --> 12:24.414
FOR, LIKE, 6 YEARS.

12:24.414 --> 12:26.046
TWO YEARS, ANDI.
ACTUALLY, NESSMAN'S

12:26.046 --> 12:27.317
BEEN HERE
FOR TWO YEARS.

12:27.317 --> 12:28.748
RIGHT. YEAH.
WELL, YOU WOULD KNOW

12:28.748 --> 12:30.350
SINCE YOU ARE HIM.

12:30.350 --> 12:32.452
HEH HEH.
Y-Y-YOU'RE HIGH.

12:32.452 --> 12:34.384
YOU'RE SO HIGH.
YOU SIT HERE AND GET
HIGH ALL DAY.

12:34.384 --> 12:35.225
I WENT OVER
OLD PAPERWORK.

12:35.225 --> 12:38.488
YOU AND LES NESSMAN
HAVE WORKED
THE SAME SHIFT

12:38.488 --> 12:39.429
EVER SINCE
HIS FIRST DAY.

12:39.429 --> 12:41.031
SO WHAT?
WE'RE SHIFT MATES.

12:41.031 --> 12:42.062
OK. YOU CLOCK
IN AND OUT

12:42.062 --> 12:43.233
AT THE EXACT SAME
TIMES.

12:43.233 --> 12:44.394
BIG WHOOPITY-DOO-DA.

12:44.394 --> 12:46.536
I CALLED
THE COFFEE SHACK.

12:47.767 --> 12:48.869
YOU DID?
YEAH. I WANTED
TO SEE

12:48.869 --> 12:50.140
IF LES NESSMAN
HAD REDEEMED

12:50.140 --> 12:51.001
HIS GIFT CARD.

12:51.001 --> 12:51.501
DID HE?
OH, YEAH.

12:51.501 --> 12:53.443
SO THEN I ASKED
FOR A DESCRIPTION
OF LES NESSMAN,

12:53.443 --> 12:54.404
AND YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT THEY SAID?

12:54.404 --> 12:57.848
UH, I DON'T KNOW.
HANDSOME AND CHARMING?

12:57.848 --> 13:01.381
LOUD AND HUSKY.

13:05.485 --> 13:06.857
HUSKY? COME ON!

13:06.857 --> 13:08.919
YOU ARE
AN EVIL GENIUS.

13:08.919 --> 13:09.920
RIGHT. I'VE BEEN
COLLECTING

13:09.920 --> 13:11.862
AN EXTRA PAYCHECK
FOR TWO YEARS, ANDI.

13:11.862 --> 13:13.423
HOW DID YOU
PULL IT OFF
FOR SO LONG?

13:13.423 --> 13:15.966
WELL, I DID HAVE
A LITTLE HELP FROM TED.

13:15.966 --> 13:17.127
TED HELPED? HOW?

13:17.127 --> 13:17.928
BY BEING
AN ABSOLUTE NIMROD

13:17.928 --> 13:19.499
AND HAVING NO IDEA
WHAT GOES ON AROUND HERE.

13:19.499 --> 13:22.532
WOW! OK.
WELL, I'M GONNA NEED

13:22.532 --> 13:24.434
LES NESSMAN'S
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

13:24.434 --> 13:25.205
ON MY DESK TOMORROW.

13:25.205 --> 13:26.436
OH, I DON'T THINK SO.
NO, NO. NO.

13:26.436 --> 13:28.138
HE'S RESPONSIBLE
FOR HALF MY PAY.

13:28.138 --> 13:29.409
SOCK, OK. I CAN'T
IN GOOD CONSCIENCE

13:29.409 --> 13:31.111
HAVE A FICTIONAL
EMPLOYEE WORKING
HERE.

13:31.111 --> 13:33.343
WHO NEEDS A GOOD CONSCIENCE?
I MEAN, IT'S OVERRATED.

13:33.343 --> 13:36.216
OK. LISTEN.
EITHER LES NESSMAN
RESIGNS,

13:36.216 --> 13:36.847
OR I FIRE HIM.

13:36.847 --> 13:38.488
YOU FI--OH.
YOU'RE GONNA FIRE HIM.

13:38.488 --> 13:40.450
COME ON.
HELP ME OUT.

13:42.422 --> 13:42.893
SOCK.

13:42.893 --> 13:45.555
ALL RIGHT. OK.
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

13:45.555 --> 13:48.198
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I RECOGNIZE YOUR PLIGHT,

13:48.198 --> 13:50.830
AND I'LL TAKE CARE
OF IT.

13:50.830 --> 13:51.401
YOU WILL?

13:51.401 --> 13:54.464
WHO'S GOT
YOUR BACK?

13:54.464 --> 13:56.136
THANK YOU, SIR.

13:57.167 --> 14:00.510
WELCOME
TO THE BENCH, SIR.

14:00.510 --> 14:02.412
HEY.

14:02.412 --> 14:03.974
HERE. CHECK
THIS BAG.

14:03.974 --> 14:05.275
OH, SURE.

14:05.275 --> 14:07.417
OH. COOL!

14:07.417 --> 14:09.479
IT'S FOR YOU.
IT'S A GEODE.

14:09.479 --> 14:10.580
IT'S GORGEOUS.

14:10.580 --> 14:12.552
IT IS SUPER-RARE.

14:12.552 --> 14:13.884
I SAW IT,
AND IT REMINDED ME

14:13.884 --> 14:15.485
OF HOW I FEEL
ABOUT YOU--

14:15.485 --> 14:17.457
SPARKLY AND WARM.

14:17.457 --> 14:20.230
IT IS WARM LITERALLY.
IT'S HOT IN MY HANDS.

14:20.230 --> 14:22.562
THAT'S BECAUSE IT'S
FROM HOME.

14:22.562 --> 14:23.333
HOME?

14:23.333 --> 14:25.265
HOME.
DOWN THERE HOME.

14:25.265 --> 14:26.566
YEAH.
HELL HOME.

14:26.566 --> 14:28.138
YEAH. MIGHT HAVE
A LITTLE BIT

14:28.138 --> 14:29.539
OF HELLFIRE
LEFT IN IT.

14:29.539 --> 14:31.972
BUT DON'T WORRY.
IT'S PERFECTLY SAFE.

14:31.972 --> 14:34.204
JUST DON'T EVER
SLEEP NEXT TO IT

14:34.204 --> 14:35.405
BECAUSE IT WILL GIVE
YOU NIGHTMARES

14:35.405 --> 14:37.547
AND DON'T EVER
MAKE WISHES UPON IT

14:37.547 --> 14:39.349
OR GET IT NEXT
TO A NUCLEAR REACTOR

14:39.349 --> 14:44.314
AND THEN JUST USE
A REGULAR DAMP CLOTH
TO CLEAN IT.

14:44.314 --> 14:46.216
I--I LOVE IT,
AND I CAN'T WAIT

14:46.216 --> 14:47.988
TO SHOW IT
TO THE GUYS.

14:47.988 --> 14:50.290
OH. SO WHAT DID
THEY THINK
ABOUT ME ANYWAY?

14:50.290 --> 14:51.361
DID THEY LIKE ME?

14:51.361 --> 14:53.994
UH, YEAH, YEAH.
I THINK THEY DID,

14:53.994 --> 14:56.066
BUT I WANTED TO TALK
TO YOU

14:56.066 --> 14:58.898
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

14:58.898 --> 15:02.032
IS THIS ABOUT
YOUR DISASTROUS
TASTE IN WOMEN?

15:02.032 --> 15:03.503
BECAUSE DON'T
WORRY ABOUT IT.

15:03.503 --> 15:07.577
I WAS THINKING MORE
ABOUT YOU COMING
AT SAM WITH A KNIFE.

15:07.577 --> 15:10.510
BUT I DIDN'T.
I CAME AT HIS BURGER
WITH THE KNIFE.

15:10.510 --> 15:13.443
I JUST WANT TO BE
CRYSTAL CLEAR
ON THE ISSUE.

15:13.443 --> 15:16.446
YOU'RE NOT DATING ME
TO KILL SAM, RIGHT?

15:16.446 --> 15:20.490
NO. BESIDES,
I DON'T NEED A KNIFE
TO KILL SAM.

15:20.490 --> 15:21.992
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

15:21.992 --> 15:23.493
UH, I JUST USE
THESE GUYS.

15:23.493 --> 15:25.625
I LIKE TO GET UP
IN THERE AND FEEL
THE HEART BEATING

15:25.625 --> 15:27.427
BEFORE I SQUISH IT
WITH MY HANDS.

15:27.427 --> 15:29.960
YOU SEE, THAT
DOESN'T MAKE ME
FEEL BETTER.

15:29.960 --> 15:33.303
OK. LET ME SAY THIS
TO YOU ONE MORE TIME, OK?

15:33.303 --> 15:36.066
WHAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN ME AND SAM
IN THE PAST

15:36.066 --> 15:36.967
IS JUST THAT.

15:36.967 --> 15:38.508
IT'S IN THE PAST.

15:38.508 --> 15:39.609
BESIDES, AFTER HANGING
OUT WITH HIM,

15:39.609 --> 15:41.311
I THINK HE'S
A REALLY GOOD GUY.

15:41.311 --> 15:44.674
I DON'T EVEN WANT TO
DESTROY HIM ANYMORE.

15:46.576 --> 15:47.547
OK.

15:47.547 --> 15:48.448
OK?

15:48.448 --> 15:50.520
THAT'S ALL I NEEDED
TO HEAR.

15:50.520 --> 15:51.481
GOOD.

15:51.481 --> 15:53.323
SO I FIGURED OUT
YOUR PROBLEM

15:53.323 --> 15:54.384
WITH CATCHING
THIS SOUL.

15:54.384 --> 15:56.486
OH? AND WHAT'S
MY PROBLEM?

15:56.486 --> 15:58.428
YOU ARE NOT
A BOXER.

15:58.428 --> 15:59.429
WOW! YOU'RE A GENIUS.

15:59.429 --> 16:00.590
YOU'RE GOING
ABOUT IT ALL WRONG, MAN.

16:00.590 --> 16:02.062
ALL YOU NEED TO DO
IS LAND ONE PUNCH.

16:02.062 --> 16:03.563
IN ORDER TO DO THAT,
YOU HAVE TO AVOID

16:03.563 --> 16:05.095
GETTING HIT
FOR AS LONG
AS POSSIBLE.

16:05.095 --> 16:09.439
NOW THERE'S NO WAY
I CAN TURN YOU
INTO A BOXER.

16:09.439 --> 16:12.072
WELL, YEAH.

16:12.072 --> 16:16.246
BUT I CAN TURN YOU
INTO A DANCER.

16:16.246 --> 16:17.547
A PITCHING MACHINE?

16:17.547 --> 16:19.479
NO, NO.
NOT A PITCHING MACHINE.

16:19.479 --> 16:20.650
YOUR NEW BEST FRIEND.

16:20.650 --> 16:22.352
USING MODERN
SPORTS TECHNOLOGY,

16:22.352 --> 16:24.114
WE'RE GONNA INCREASE
YOUR SPEED

16:24.114 --> 16:25.715
AND HELP YOU AVOID
GETTING HIT.

16:25.715 --> 16:27.457
THIS IS TOTALLY
STUPID.

16:27.457 --> 16:29.559
GOOD ENOUGH
FOR ME.

16:29.559 --> 16:30.520
OHH!

16:30.520 --> 16:31.521
HEY. I DODGED IT.

16:31.521 --> 16:33.393
UH-HUH. GOOD JOB.

16:33.393 --> 16:36.166
HEY! YEAH!

16:36.166 --> 16:38.498
I'M DOING IT.
I'M DANCING.

16:38.498 --> 16:40.530
I KNOW. I SEE IT.

16:40.530 --> 16:41.471
YEAH!

16:41.471 --> 16:44.434
OH, WHOA!
WHAT THE HELL, MAN?

16:44.434 --> 16:46.436
I'M THE LEFT HOOK.

16:46.436 --> 16:47.607
OH. WELL...

16:47.607 --> 16:48.478
OHH!

16:48.478 --> 16:49.709
EYES ON THE PRIZE,
SAMMY.

16:49.709 --> 16:51.681
EYES ON THE PRIZE.

16:51.681 --> 16:52.782
AHH, YI!

16:52.782 --> 16:54.544
OK. AAH!

16:54.544 --> 16:56.646
OHH!

16:56.646 --> 16:58.688
STOP IT!

16:58.688 --> 17:00.490
Sock: ALL RIGHT.
HOW YOU FEELING?
YOU FEELING PUMPED?

17:00.490 --> 17:01.691
YOU SHOULD
FEEL PUMPED.
WINNERS FEEL PUMPED.

17:01.691 --> 17:03.653
NO. I AM NOT PUMPED,
AND YOU WOULDN'T BE EITHER

17:03.653 --> 17:05.755
IF YOU KNEW WHAT
WAS AHEAD OF YOU.

17:05.755 --> 17:07.427
OK. ALL RIGHT.

17:08.558 --> 17:09.359
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

17:09.359 --> 17:11.531
I WANT YOU TO HIT
MY HAND AS HARD
AS YOU CAN, ALL RIGHT?

17:11.531 --> 17:12.662
HEY. DON'T BE SHY.
COME ON.

17:12.662 --> 17:14.534
DROP A LOAD
OF SAMMY ON ME.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.506
I CAN HANDLE IT.

17:16.506 --> 17:18.568
WOULD YOU QUIT
SCREWING AROUND
AND HIT MY HAND

17:18.568 --> 17:20.039
AS HARD AS YOU CAN? GO.

17:20.039 --> 17:20.770
THAT WAS IT.

17:20.770 --> 17:22.442
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

17:22.442 --> 17:23.543
WOW! YOU ARE WEAK.
SOCK, NOT NOW.

17:23.543 --> 17:25.615
YOU GOT THE PUNCHING POWER
OF A DRUNKEN BABY.

17:25.615 --> 17:26.816
KNOCK IT OFF.
I HOPE YOU THROW THE BONE

17:26.816 --> 17:28.078
BETTER THAN YOU THROW
THE FIST.

17:28.078 --> 17:29.679
I FEEL BAD FOR ANDI.
SHUT UP!

17:29.679 --> 17:31.251
HEY! WAIT!
SOCK, STOP IT!

17:31.251 --> 17:32.452
ALL RIGHT. SEE WHAT
I DID THERE,
SEE WHAT I DID?

17:32.452 --> 17:34.624
I GOT INSIDE YOUR HEAD.
YOU LOST YOUR CONCENTRATION.

17:34.624 --> 17:36.556
I SLIPPED A SHOT
IN ON YOU.

17:36.556 --> 17:37.287
SO.
SO?

17:37.287 --> 17:38.528
THAT'S WHAT YOU GOT TO
DO TO RED, MAN.

17:38.528 --> 17:41.391
YOU GOT TO TALK
A LITTLE TRASH,
RATTLE HIS CAGE.

17:41.391 --> 17:43.293
BOXING REQUIRES FOCUS.

17:43.293 --> 17:44.664
YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE?

17:44.664 --> 17:45.665
IT'S LIKE HAVING SEX.

17:45.665 --> 17:47.267
ALL RIGHT. EVERYTHING'S
GOING GOOD, RIGHT?

17:47.267 --> 17:48.638
YOU'RE GETTING
YOUR GROOVE ON,
CHUGGING ALONG.

17:48.638 --> 17:51.601
IN COMES THE TALKING,
THE HINTS, THE TIPS,
THE CRITICIZING.

17:51.601 --> 17:53.603
NEXT THING YOU KNOW,
YOU'VE LOST THAT
CONCENTRATION,

17:53.603 --> 17:58.578
YOU'RE LOCKED
IN THE BATHROOM YELLING
AT YOUR OWN LAP!

17:58.578 --> 17:59.579
THAT COULD WORK.

17:59.579 --> 18:03.283
IT WILL WORK. YEAH.

18:07.587 --> 18:11.391
WOW. DIDN'T THINK
YOU HAD IT
IN YOU, KID.

18:11.391 --> 18:12.322
YOU PROVED
YOUR POINT.

18:12.322 --> 18:13.693
YOU'RE NOT
A PUSHOVER.

18:13.693 --> 18:16.826
ANOTHER TIME,
I'D BUY YOU A BEER,

18:16.826 --> 18:18.298
BUT I'M A BUSY MAN,

18:18.298 --> 18:20.770
AND I'M NOT GOING
BACK TO HELL.

18:20.770 --> 18:23.333
I'M NOT HERE
TO DRINK BEER.

18:23.333 --> 18:25.375
I'M HERE TO FIGHT.

18:29.839 --> 18:31.441
OK. REMEMBER, SAM.
FLOAT LIKE A BUTTERFLY

18:31.441 --> 18:34.584
AND LET YOUR WORDS
STING LIKE A HATEFUL,
SARCASTIC BEE.

18:34.584 --> 18:35.815
AND REMEMBER, DANCE,
DANCE IN THERE.

18:35.815 --> 18:38.448
DANCE IT OUT, ALL RIGHT?
KEEP IT LOOSE.

18:38.448 --> 18:40.190
ALL RIGHT.

18:42.892 --> 18:44.123
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

18:44.123 --> 18:47.126
MOVING!
I'M NOT GONNA MAKE
THIS EASY ON YOU.

18:47.126 --> 18:48.828
WHEELHOUSE TIME.
GET IN HIS WHEELHOUSE.

18:48.828 --> 18:49.729
WHEELHOUSE. YEAH.

18:49.729 --> 18:51.461
I GOT TO SAY, KID.
I'M IMPRESSED.

18:51.461 --> 18:52.562
YOU GOT STONES
FOR DAYS.

18:52.562 --> 18:58.508
YEAH. WELL, YOU'RE
JUST ANOTHER BUM,
RIGHT? HUH?

18:58.508 --> 18:59.609
HUH?

18:59.609 --> 19:00.770
WHAT DID YOU
CALL ME?

19:00.770 --> 19:01.571
YOU HEARD ME.

19:01.571 --> 19:03.513
WHY DON'T YOU ASK
THE 29 GUYS
I PUT TO BED

19:03.513 --> 19:04.514
HOW MUCH OF
A BUM I AM?

19:04.514 --> 19:05.645
I'D RATHER ASK
THE GUY WHO BEAT YOU

19:05.645 --> 19:07.477
BECAUSE YOU THREW
THE FIGHT, HUH?

19:07.477 --> 19:09.879
YEAH. YOU WEREN'T SO
TOUGH ON HIM, HUH?

19:09.879 --> 19:11.721
NICE, SAMMY.
STICK AND MOVE.
STICK AND MOVE.

19:11.721 --> 19:13.853
WHY DON'T YOU
SHUT YOUR MOUTH?

19:13.853 --> 19:16.186
HA HA HA!
HA HA HA!

19:16.186 --> 19:18.558
HEY, SOCK.
HOW MUCH MONEY WE GOT?

19:18.558 --> 19:20.530
I DON'T KNOW.
LET ME FIND OUT.

19:21.661 --> 19:23.233
$13, SAM.

19:23.233 --> 19:23.733
WHAT DO YOU SAY, RED?

19:23.733 --> 19:26.936
$13 ENOUGH TO BUY
YOU OFF THESE DAYS?

19:26.936 --> 19:29.599
OH, YEAH.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:29.599 --> 19:33.543
MAYBE YOU COULD
PAY ME TO BEAT YOU.

19:33.543 --> 19:34.544
HA HA HA!

19:34.544 --> 19:37.277
UNH! UNH!

19:41.811 --> 19:43.483
OHH!

19:53.593 --> 19:55.465
RUN, SAM!

19:55.465 --> 19:57.767
OH, OH, OH!

20:05.275 --> 20:07.537
DID HE JUST KNOCK
HIMSELF OUT?

20:07.537 --> 20:10.209
YES, I BELIEVE HE DID.

20:29.399 --> 20:30.700
♪ PERMIT ME
TO INTRODUCE MYSELF ♪

20:30.700 --> 20:33.303
♪ THE NAME IS MR. KICKS... ♪

20:33.303 --> 20:37.637
MAYBE YOU, UH, MIGHT
WANT TO TAKE THE GLOVES OFF.

20:40.470 --> 20:41.841
FORGET IT.
IT'S TOO HARD.

20:41.841 --> 20:43.473
HEY, MAN. I GOT TO
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

20:43.473 --> 20:44.714
YOU WERE AWESOME
BACK THERE.

20:44.714 --> 20:45.615
SOCK, HE'S--
LISTEN, LISTEN.

20:45.615 --> 20:47.477
I MEAN, IT'S AWFUL
THAT YOU PUMMELED
MY FRIEND

20:47.477 --> 20:48.548
INTO THE GROUND
AND EVERYTHING,

20:48.548 --> 20:49.719
BUT, OH, MY GOD.
WOW.

20:49.719 --> 20:51.551
I'VE NEVER SEEN
A HUMAN BEING DEAL
OUT PUNISHMENT

20:51.551 --> 20:53.823
LIKE THAT
IN MY LIFE.
IT WAS UNREAL.

20:53.823 --> 20:54.554
THANKS. THANKS.

20:54.554 --> 20:56.356
TO BE FAIR, YOUR BUDDY
COULD TAKE A PUNCH

20:56.356 --> 20:57.557
WITH THE BEST OF THEM.

20:57.557 --> 20:58.458
THANKS.
THERE YOU GO.

20:58.458 --> 21:00.760
IT'S NICE TO BE GOOD
AT SOMETHING,
RIGHT, SAMMY? RIGHT?

21:00.760 --> 21:02.592
SORRY ABOUT WHAT
HAPPENED BACK THERE.

21:02.592 --> 21:05.395
I MEAN, YOU PRESSED
MY BUTTONS PRETTY GOOD,

21:05.395 --> 21:07.337
AND I GUESS I BLEW
A GASKET.

21:07.337 --> 21:07.737
HEH HEH. YEAH.

21:07.737 --> 21:10.770
THAT'S--THAT'S WHY
THEY CALLED ME RED,
YOU KNOW?

21:10.770 --> 21:14.674
I'D LOSE MY TEMPER,
AND THAT'S ALL I COULD SEE.

21:14.674 --> 21:17.276
RED.
RED. BUT THAT'S NOT

21:17.276 --> 21:19.749
WHAT I'M ABOUT.

21:19.749 --> 21:22.912
NOT ANYMORE.

21:22.912 --> 21:25.915
[SQUEAK]

21:25.915 --> 21:27.987
BEAT HALF THE GUYS
ON THIS WALL.

21:27.987 --> 21:30.660
OH, YEAH?
YEAH.

21:30.660 --> 21:31.721
I SHOULD BE UP THERE.

21:31.721 --> 21:33.663
HOW COME YOU'RE NOT?

21:33.663 --> 21:37.627
DISGRACED MYSELF.
DISGRACED THE GAME.

21:37.627 --> 21:40.530
TOOK A BRIBE,
AND THAT'S ALL SHE WROTE.

21:40.530 --> 21:41.571
WELL, IF YOU WERE
SO GOOD,

21:41.571 --> 21:43.302
WHY'D YOU THROW
THE FIGHT?

21:43.302 --> 21:45.635
A GUY COMES TO ME,
HE, UH...

21:45.635 --> 21:49.439
OFFERS ME MORE MONEY THAN
WHAT THE PRIZE MONEY WAS.

21:49.439 --> 21:50.740
I GOT GREEDY.

21:50.740 --> 21:55.545
WOUND UP BEING
THE BIGGEST MISTAKE
I EVER MADE.

21:55.545 --> 21:57.917
FIXING TO CHANGE
THAT, THOUGH.

21:57.917 --> 22:01.050
SO. YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO SEND ME BACK
TO HELL, HUH?

22:01.050 --> 22:03.593
DON'T REALLY
HAVE A CHOICE.
DEVIL OWNS MY SOUL.

22:03.593 --> 22:07.627
SOONER OR LATER,
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
CAPTURE YOU.

22:07.627 --> 22:09.659
PROBABLY LATER.

22:10.630 --> 22:13.032
LOOK. I'M NOT LOOKING
TO HURT ANYBODY

22:13.032 --> 22:15.505
OR KILL ANYBODY, EH?

22:15.505 --> 22:20.370
I GOT ONE GOAL
AND ONE GOAL ONLY--

22:20.370 --> 22:22.412
WIN THAT TITLE.

22:22.412 --> 22:23.773
FIGURE IT WILL TAKE ME
7 FIGHTS.

22:23.773 --> 22:26.746
FIRST ONE IS NEXT WEEK
IN VEGAS,

22:26.746 --> 22:29.549
SO I THINK I COULD HAVE
THE WHOLE THING WRAPPED UP

22:29.549 --> 22:31.020
IN TWO YEARS TOPS.

22:31.020 --> 22:32.422
SO...

22:32.422 --> 22:35.585
SO. I GOT
A PROPOSITION.

22:35.585 --> 22:37.427
LET ME DO THIS.

22:37.427 --> 22:38.728
GIVE ME THE TWO YEARS.

22:38.728 --> 22:42.632
I WIN THE TITLE,
THEN I'LL GO BACK
TO HELL WILLINGLY.

22:42.632 --> 22:43.733
I'D BE HAPPY TO.

22:43.733 --> 22:45.665
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

22:45.665 --> 22:48.498
LOOK. EITHER YOU GO BACK
WITH ME IN THAT RING

22:48.498 --> 22:50.770
AND I BEAT YOU
TO A PULP AGAIN,

22:50.770 --> 22:53.503
OR YOU CAN TAKE
MY PROPOSITION
TO YOUR BOSS

22:53.503 --> 22:55.575
AND SEE WHAT HE HAS
TO SAY ABOUT IT.

22:55.575 --> 22:59.949
WELL, I GUESS I'LL RUN IT
UP THE FLAGPOLE.

22:59.949 --> 23:02.482
YEAH. GOOD CHOICE.

23:08.718 --> 23:09.819
THIS ISN'T FOR ME.

23:09.819 --> 23:11.591
I JUST GOT OFF
THE PHONE WITH
CORPORATE.

23:11.591 --> 23:12.662
AW. HOW IS CORPORATE?

23:12.662 --> 23:14.123
UH, NOT GOOD,
ACTUALLY.

23:14.123 --> 23:16.526
IT SEEMS THAT THEY
GOT A CALL FROM
A MR. LES NESSMAN.

23:16.526 --> 23:18.397
OH.
YEAH.

23:18.397 --> 23:19.569
HE THREATENED
TO FILE

23:19.569 --> 23:20.570
